originalText.text: We were in Soho doing the Top view tour so we got a corn dog, chilli cheese hotdog, and 2 drinks for $25. The corn dog was nice and crunchy and my son thought the hotdog was small but tasty. Probably would not get food again, to expensive.

originalText.text: Not only did the food make me sick, I was supposed to be charged 4$ each for my hot dog and sausage and I got a credit card charge of 23$!!!! They are scammers, I would never buy from them again. Don’t give these scammers your money. Their hot dogs and sausages also sit out all day. Nothing is stored in a cooler until it’s ready to be served. However I wanted to experience a hot dog stand while I was visiting NYC and they were the only stand open. It’s supposed to be Halal and that’s not very halal!!! Shame on them!!!

To be clear this was a single location near grand central terminal, but I do not see that specific location on maps. Have included image of exact stand & location.

Summary in case TLDR;
The main reason for this review is I would like to warn people to pay attention if you are using a card to purchase, because you may get overcharged

Details:
I ordered a regular chili dog from this hotdog stand.  I was given a regular chili dog.  However I was charged for a premium sausage chili dog ($15) which was not what I received or ordered.  I went back to the stand and talked to the vender a couple hours later when I noticed the discrepancy.  The man called me a liar and refused to refund the difference or make it right.  I know it is kind of silly to complain about 8 dollars or so but the main issue was the entire experience seemed like he had a speech ready for it and must have done this sort of scam before.  .
